article.headline: Georgia Southern 101, Flagler 67
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. (AP) -- Jimmy Tobias scored 22 points to lead Georgia Southern to a 101-67 win over Flagler on Tuesday night. The Saints (4-5) held a 20-16 lead with 10 minutes left in the first half. But the Eagles (6-3) went on a 19-2 run and took a 39-18 advantage into halftime before building their lead to 38 points in the second half. Donte Gennie scored 14 points and Louis Graham added 11 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for Georgia Southern. Matt Fields had 11 points and 10 rebounds, while Dwayne Foreman had eight assists and no turnovers. Sam Jozenville led Flagler with 16 points.
